Thank God for Youtube, since I got to see the episode.

Of course I must speak of the almost hug. Casey wants a hug and Derek shakes her hand instead.

I found this incredibly dasey-esque. I mean, all the times Derek takes every oppurtunity to touch Casey, and when it's out in the open he shirks away. He's so shy. And did anyone else note the hurt look on Casey's face when Derek didn't hug her? Because she WANTED TO HUG HIM! 

Definite Dasey!

I posted it about a week ago.
Love, Tarryn
Okay, call me crazy, but I think I found another show to ship for stepcest. O.o lol!
Watched it (abslutely awesome episode; one of my favorites) on Disney, and took some screen shots. [=

Compiled by my wonderful friend Jo, who is so adament in Dasey, it's almost scary (ALMOST). She is GENIUS!

10 reasons why Dasey is going to happen

1. Ash said so. (Eat that, Dasey haters! HA!)

2. Mikey wrote one of the USTiest Dasey episodes ever.

3. Have you seen the way he looks at her?!

4. Over half of the LWD watching comunity is analyzing the episodes of LWD over and over and over to look for Dasey signs, and we've found one/more in every. Single. Episode.

5. If there's ever a reason at all to put his arm around Casey's shoulders/waist, stand next to her, or come into physical contact, he'll take it.

6. The Hula-Hoop Moment. Need I say more?

7. She cried. Derek refused to go to Spain. Helloooooo?!

8. Sam; Derek didn't want him to date Casey, 'I'm not losing my best friend' my foot, Derek. Scott; He was going nutso, you hear me?! NUTSO!!! Max; He continues to prank him, and in 'It's Our Party', he messed up her chances with Max by teaching her about football the wrong way.

9. He was happy about her wearing his flippin' shirt.

10. She grabbed him by the shirt and threw him on the bed. I'm going to end this reason now before I go into detail of how kinky that is.  (x3)

Look at my awesome new Dasey picture!



Credit to 62021631 Myspace

Well, knock me over. Derek quit his job! For Casey! 
... 
QUIT HIS JOB FOR CASEY! And they are actually beginning to get along, which could lead to them hanging out more, which WILL lead to them developing feelings for each other, which will lead to DASEY! 

I must say, I loooved the eppy. Any comments? 

Love, Tarryn

Okay, so we've all pined away, poking at any possible sign that Casey and Derek even remotely got along -because then that totally meant that their views of each other were changing..lol- replaying clips, and watching fanvids; reading fanfiction. None of us ever really wanted to let the relentless words of the Non-Dasey shippers get to us. -Omg, Dasey is so never going to happen. Get over it. Like, ew, it's incest. They'd never show it on Disney.- Blah, blah, blah. But deep in our hearts we wondered if it really was impossible, even though we would never stop shipping.

But I must say, it's becoming clearer that Dasey is almost positive to happen. I mean, everything that's been going on with the show. Casey and Derek; the commercials, the pictures, the Fanfiction Dasey podcase that is supposed to -hopefully-  air in September, based off of Out of the Blue by degrassichick. It's gotta happen!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!

..
..
..
I just wish it would happen sooooonnnneeerrr!!! *whines*

Love, Tarryn
